Metadata-Version: 1.1
Name: ddict
Version: 0.1.2
Summary: Dict class with dot notation (like attributes) for accessing nested values
Home-page: https://github.com/rbehzadan/ddict
Author: Reza Behzadan
Author-email: rbehzadan@gmail.com
License: MIT
Description: |Build Status| |Coverage Status| # DotAccessDict
        
        DotAccessDict class can handle nested dictionaries with arbitray number
        of dicts and lists, nested inside each other.
        
        Usage:
        ~~~~~~
        
        .. code:: python
        
            >>> from ddict import DotAccessDict
            >>> d = DotAccessDict()
            >>> d
            {}
            >>> d.person
            {}
            >>> d.person.name = 'Jack'
            >>> d
            {'person': {'name': 'Jack'}}
            >>> d['person']['name']
            'Jack'
            >>> d['person'].name
            'Jack'
            >>> d.person['name']
            'Jack'
            >>> joe = dict(name='Joe', age=18)
            >>> d.person.brothers = [joe, 'John', 'Pat']
            >>> d.person.brothers[0].age
            18
            >>> d.get('person.brothers[1]')
            'John'
            >>> d.set('person.brothers[2]', 'James')
            >>> d.person.brothers[2]
            'James'
            >>> d.flatten()
            {'person.brothers[0].age': 18,
             'person.brothers[0].name': 'Joe',
             'person.brothers[1]': 'John',
             'person.brothers[2]': 'James',
             'person.name': 'Jack'}
        
        Similar works:
        ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
        
        -  https://github.com/mewwts/addict
        -  https://github.com/makinacorpus/easydict
        -  https://github.com/drgrib/dotmap
        
